<span class=dateline>August    29, 2003</span> - Alan VanCouvering, the Community Relations Manager for Lost Dungeons of Norrath, has provided us with the answers to our first three questions in this new bi-weekly feature. It will alternate with our Ask SOE for EQII and we hope you enjoy it. If you have any questions for the next edition, please send them to <A HREF="mailto:lepidus@vaultnetwork.com">lepidus@vaultnetwork.com</A> with "LDoN Question" clearly in the subject line.<BR>
<BR>
Not only did they send us the Q&A answers. The good folks at SOE also provided us with three exclusive screenshots from the new Mistmoore dungeon. You can see them all to the right, in the article, and in the Media Page below.<BR>
<BR>
Finally, if you wish to comment on what you've read, check out <A HREF="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=55600984&replies=0">this thread</A> on the <A HREF="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5001">EQ General Board</A>.<BR>
<BR>
<HR><BR>
<CENTER><B>Lost Dungeons of Norrath Mini Q&A #1<BR>
With Alan VanCouvering</B></CENTER><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Lepidus:</B> The much-anticipated dynamic dungeon system is one of the coolest features about Lost Dungeons. Do you think you could explain that feature a little more?<BR>
<BR>
<B>Alan VanCouvering:</B> An adventure starts with the gathering of your group.  You'll get together and then find a Wayfarer camp.  Talking to the Wayfarers reveals that they have a task that they would like you to complete.  The Wayfarer estimates the ability of your group and asks you to complete a task that he believes is within your ability, but your group leader can ask for a harder task if your group is feeling brave.<BR>
<BR>
As soon as you accept the task, a dungeon instance is created.  This is a complete dungeon, with NPCs, objects, and everything.  Only your group can enter this dungeon, and they can come and go as they wish for as long as the zone remains.<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="http://eqvaultmedia.ign.com/eqvault/image/t_w1_ldon_1.jpg"><IMG SRC="http://eqvaultmedia.ign.com/eqvault/image/t_w1_ldon_1.jpg"></A></CENTER><BR>
<BR>
Once you have accepted the adventure, your group has a specified amount of time to get into the zone.  Portals into the various zone themes are in old world zones, and the time given is more than enough to reach these portals.  Once you enter the dungeon, you have a specific amount of time to complete your task.  All of this information is available in the Adventure window (which any group member can open at any time using Alt-V).<BR>
<BR>
As you travel these dungeons, you will notice that NPCs generally do not respawn.  To achieve your goal you have to keep moving forward into the dungeon.  Once you complete your adventure (or time runs out), the dungeon instance disappears.  Any player characters or PC corpses are moved to the portal where they entered.<BR>
<BR>
This allows us a lot of flexibility and control over what we present to the players.  Knowing what level their group is, we can be much more certain that they face a challenge and that they are rewarded appropriately.  Also, with each completed adventure a character earns points.  They can save these points to purchase any item they are offered by the Wayfarer Merchant.  This allows players to work towards a reward of their choosing.<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="http://mediaviewer.ign.com/ignMediaPage.jsp?media_id=1800280&article_id=436031&channel_id=253&page_title=First+Bi-Weekly+LDoN+Q%26A+%2B+Screenshots%21&adtag=network%3Dign%26size%3D468x60%26channel%3Deqvault%26site%3Deqvault_hub%26channel%3Dfeatures%26type%3Dpartner"><IMG SRC="http://eqvaultmedia.ign.com/eqvault/image/t_w1_ldon_2.jpg"></A></CENTER><BR>
<BR>
<B>Lepidus:</B> Each expansion advanced the story of Norrath a little more. Specifically, what will Lost Dungeons do to advance it further? Will any of these story advancements have server wide implications?<BR>
<BR>
<B>Alan VanCouvering:</B> Well, a lot of the initial story has been revealed on our web site (www.lostdungeonsofnorrath.com).  This tells you a bit about how the Wayfarers Brotherhood began.  But there is a lot more lore tied into the dungeons, and you can only hear those stories as you travel the path of adventure in game.<BR>

